commit.message: Relax threaded profile counts (seems to vary a lot on CI)
Don't use Py_XSETREF, it's a private API

Fix for thread-unsafe crash. Profiler state now stored in thread locals.

State is in a PyObject that's passed to the PyEval_SetProfile function.
This is stored in the thread variables, and passed back whenever the
callback is made.

In this way, setstatprofile can be called from different threads, the
profiling sessions are completely isolated.
Add test-case for segfault during threaded use
Install twine using system pip, not cibw pip
Add Pip fixes by using get-pip.py every time
